DKSH Holdings (Malaysia) Berhad Key Developments

DKSH Holdings (Malaysia) Berhad Approves Final Single Tier Dividend for the Financial Year Ended December 31, 2016
May 24 17
DKSH Holdings (Malaysia) Berhad announced that at its AGM held on May 24, 2017, shareholders approved the payment of a final single tier dividend of 9.5 sen per share for the financial year ended December 31, 2016.


DKSH Holdings (Malaysia) Berhad Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 24 17
DKSH Holdings (Malaysia) Berhad announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company announced revenue was MYR 1,369,668,000 compared to MYR 1,332,797,000 for the same period a year ago. Profit from operations was MYR 15,277,000 compared to MYR 17,301,000 for the same period a year ago. Profit before taxation was MYR 13,509,000 compared to MYR 15,679,000 for the same period a year ago. Net profit attributable to owners of the parent company was MYR 10,046,000 compared to MYR 11,270,000 for the same period a year ago. Earnings per share were 6.37 sen compared to 7.15 sen for the same period a year ago. Net cash flows used in operating activities was MYR 108,001,000 compared to MYR 105,802,000 for the same period a year ago. Purchase of property, plant and equipment was MYR 1,354,000 compared to MYR 2,130,000 for the same period a year ago. Revenue growth results from underlying organic growth in existing clients. The lower profit before tax performance is a result of the change in product mix and temporary additional warehousing cost.


DKSH Holdings (Malaysia) Berhad Announces Retirement of Alexander Stuart Davy as Independent and Non Executive Member of Nomination Committee
May 24 17
DKSH Holdings (Malaysia) Berhad announced retirement of Mr. Alexander Stuart Davy as independent and non executive member of nomination committee, effective May 24, 2017.


