Product Specialist - Pharmaceutical (based in Johor)

DKSH Malaysia Sdn Bhd












			Min 1 year (Junior Executive) 
		








			Malaysia - Johor		















 JOB DESCRIPTION
 DKSH's Business Unit Healthcare is the leading partner for healthcare companies seeking to grow their business in Asia.With our marketing and sales capabilities and understanding supported by regulatory affairs, customer care centers, state-of-the-art GMP-compliant distribution centers and leading-edge IT infrastructure, we offer a wide range of Market Expansion Services from product registration, marketing, sales to quality distribution. Products available through DKSH include ethical pharmaceuticals, over-the-counter (OTC) and consumer health as well as medial devices are delivered to multiple professional healthcare outlets.Our strong position in Malaysia healthcare industry is the result of a variety of factors - our commitment to quality management, the confidence that our business partners and customers have in our people, operations, leading-edge IT servies and business solutions, our market coverage and reach, the capability to commercialize our partners' business, and our innovative customer service centers. We continuously strive to become an ever better integrated service provider and to consistently deliver excellence to our stakeholders. For more information , please visit www.dksh.com.my/servicesJob responsibilitiesTo ensure that all sales objectives set are met through continuous and regular service to customersResponsible for all the sales and promotion of pharmaceutical products to hospitals channelTo ensure all sales objectives set are met through continuous and regular service to customersRegular visits to targeted customersEnsure product detailing to customersMeeting the required minimum number of eight (8) visits per dayTo implement all promotional activities and ensuring the expected sales are metUpdate and maintain the Echoplus database system on daily basisTo participate and support any teamwork activities from time to timeManaging both Government and Private Hospitals and Standalone Specialist Clinics Job requirementsBachelor's degree in Medical Science or Life Science or equivalentExperience around 1- 2 years pharmaceutical sales experience or any sales related capacity is preferredExperience selling in Pharmacy and with General Practitioner would be an added advantagePossess initiative and drive to excel in a highly competitive marketGood communication skills, pleasant personality and good working attitudePossess own transport with a valid driving licenseDisciplined and able to work independentlyFresh graduates from the relevant background are encouraged to apply  


 



